---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Astronomy & Planets — Space Terms That Score Big"
  description="Astronomy and planet words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. JUPITER (16pts), NEBULA (8pts), QUASAR (15pts). Space vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble astronomy words, jupiter scrabble points, quasar scrabble, nebula scrabble, planet words scrabble, space vocabulary scrabble, cosmos words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Astronomy & Planets — Space Terms That Score Big","description":"Astronomy and planet words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. JUPITER (16pts), NEBULA (8pts), QUASAR (15pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-astronomy-planets"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is QUASAR a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! QUASAR scores 15 points (Q=10, U=1, A=1, S=1, A=1, R=1). The Q=10 tile dominates this score. QUASAR is one of the best Q-with-U words — 6 letters, natural spelling, and a massive 15-point base."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is JUPITER worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"JUPITER scores 16 points (J=8, U=1, P=3, I=1, T=1, E=1, R=1). The J=8 tile carries this 7-letter planet name into bingo territory — play all 7 tiles for 66 total points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play NEBULA in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. NEBULA scores 8 points (N=1, E=1, B=3, U=1, L=1, A=1). The B=3 tile adds value to this 6-letter cosmic cloud. Hooks with E (NEBULAE, 10pts) and S (NEBULAS, 9pts) for extended plays."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Astronomy & Planets — Space Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Launch your Scrabble score into orbit with astronomy vocabulary. Space terms pack premium tiles like Q, J, and X into words that feel natural — QUASAR, JUPITER, and NEBULA are all valid plays waiting on your rack.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">16 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">JUPITER</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">QUASAR</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">NEBULA</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ZENITH</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Space Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">JUPITER — 16 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">J=8, U=1, P=3, I=1, T=1, E=1, R=1 · 7 letters · J-powered bingo</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The largest planet delivers the largest score. J=8 and P=3 provide 11 of the 16 base points, and at 7 letters JUPITER qualifies for the bingo bonus — a stellar 66-point total when played from your rack.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🪐 JUPITER</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">16 pts · J=8, U=1, P=3, I=1, T=1, E=1, R=1 · Bingo</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✨ QUASAR</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 pts · Q=10, U=1, A=1, S=1, A=1, R=1 · Q word</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌌 NEBULA</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · N=1, E=1, B=3, U=1, L=1, A=1 · Hookable</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ ZENITH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">18 pts · Z=10, E=1, N=1, I=1, T=1, H=4 · Z+H power</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Astronomy Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">COMET</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PULSAR</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ORBIT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">STELLAR</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GALAXY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">COSMIC</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Space Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">QUASAR is your Q-word lifeline:</span> Q=10 with U naturally following — QUASAR uses the Q tile in a 6-letter word with otherwise common letters (U, A, S, A, R). One of the most reliable Q plays available.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">JUPITER is the ultimate J-bingo:</span> J=8 plus P=3 in a natural 7-letter word. When J appears on your rack with common letters, hunt for JUPITER — the 66-point total (16+50 bonus) is worth playing for.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ZENITH hides Z+H value:</span> Z=10 and H=4 combine for 14 points from just 2 tiles. ZENITH scores 18 from 6 letters — memorise this for when Z and H co-exist on your rack.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Astronomy vocabulary is a <span class="text-white font-medium">premium tile paradise</span>. Q in QUASAR, J in JUPITER, Z in ZENITH, X in GALAXY — the rarest, highest-value tiles all find natural homes in space terminology. Memorise these for instant access to your rack's hardest letters.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-chemistry-elements/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Chemistry Elements</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-electricity/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Electricity</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-geology/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Geology</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-astronomy/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Astronomy</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-science/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Science</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-q-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Q Words in Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid space word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
